block-definition.s: closest words to %'features' in language %'language' $nl and include distances %'include distances'
block-definition.comment: Reports all the words sorted by closeness to 'features'. Optionally can report pairs of words and distances. Distances are measured using cosine similarity.

input.options: Chinese English Finnish French German Greek Hindi Indonesian Italian Japanese Lithuanian Portuguese Sinhalese Spanish Swedish

block-definition.comment: Reports a list of 300 numbers that "describes" the word. You can choose among 15 languages or leave it blank and use the default language. To learn about these numbers see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Word_embedding

input.options: Chinese English Finnish French German Greek Hindi Indonesian Italian Japanese Lithuanian Portuguese Sinhalese Spanish Swedish

custom-block.s: wait for word embeddings in language %txt %br or use this word embeddings url %txt

block-definition.comment: Reports a sorted version of the list in its first input slot, using the comparison function in the second input slot. For a list of numbers, using < as the comparison function will sort from low to high; using > will sort from high to low.

block-definition.s: make analogies %'words' with score less than %'threshold' $nl in language %'language'
block-definition.comment: Finds the distances between pairs taken from the incoming list of 4 words and if less than threshold reports them.

input.options: Chinese English Finnish French German Greek Hindi Indonesian Italian Japanese Lithuanian Portuguese Sinhalese Spanish Swedish

custom-block.comment: Possibly one of the pairs needs to be reversed.

scripts.comment: An alternative using Euclidean distance is to use cosine similarity. Try replacing the distance calculations with the following.

block-definition.s: Find analogies among %'number of words' words near %'word' $nl keeping those with a score less than %'threshold' $nl in language %'language'
block-definition.comment: Reports all analogies with a distance score less than 'threshold' taken from the 'number of words' closest to 'word'.

input.options: Chinese English Finnish French German Greek Hindi Indonesian Italian Japanese Lithuanian Portuguese Sinhalese Spanish Swedish
